==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tiebeam
<hw>Tie"beam`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>A
beam acting as a tie, as at the bottom of a pair of principal rafters,
to prevent them from thrusting out the wall. See <xex>Illust.</xex> of
<xex>Timbers</xex>, under <er>Roof</er>.</def>
<rj><au>Gwilt.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tien an men</ent>⟦br⟧
